<% layout('layouts/boilerplate') %>

<section class="py-4 py-md-5">
  <div class="row justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-lg-10 col-xl-9">
      <header class="mb-4 mb-md-5">
        <h1 class="h2 fw-bold" style="letter-spacing: -0.01em">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="text-muted mb-0">
          Last updated: <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString() %>
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm" style="border-radius: 1.25rem">
        <div class="card-body p-4 p-md-5">
          <p>
            Welcome to DRIVVA ("we", "us", or "our"). We respect your privacy
            and are committed to protecting your personal information. This
            Privacy Policy explains what data we collect, how we use it, and the
            choices you have. By using DRIVVA, you agree to the practices
            described here.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">1. Information We Collect</h2>
          <p>
            We collect information to operate DRIVVA effectively and provide you
            with the best experience.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <b>Account Data:</b> name, email, password (hashed), profile
              details.
            </li>
            <li>
              <b>Content & Activity:</b> listings you create, reviews, likes,
              bookmarks.
            </li>
            <li>
              <b>Usage Data:</b> pages viewed, actions taken, device and browser
              info, IP address, timestamps.
            </li>
            <li>
              <b>Cookies & Similar Tech:</b> used for session management,
              analytics, and preferences.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Provide, operate, and improve the platform and features.</li>
            <li>Authenticate users and secure accounts.</li>
            <li>Personalize content and remember preferences.</li>
            <li>
              Monitor performance, debug issues, and prevent abuse or fraud.
            </li>
            <li>
              Communicate service updates, security alerts, and account
              notifications.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">3. Legal Bases</h2>
          <p>
            We process your data under legitimate interests, contract necessity
            (to provide DRIVVA), and your consent where required (e.g., optional
            cookies).
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">4. Sharing & Disclosure</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <b>Service Providers:</b> infrastructure, analytics, and email
              services under contractual obligations.
            </li>
            <li>
              <b>Legal:</b> to comply with law, enforce terms, or protect
              rights, safety, and property.
            </li>
            <li>
              <b>Business Transfers:</b> in connection with a merger,
              acquisition, or asset sale.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">5. Cookies</h2>
          <p>
            We use essential cookies for login sessions and functionality, and
            may use analytics cookies to understand usage. You can control
            cookies via your browser settings.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">6. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>
            We retain personal data as long as necessary to provide DRIVVA and
            for legitimate business or legal purposes. You may request deletion
            as described below.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">7. Your Rights</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Access a copy of your personal data.</li>
            <li>Request correction or deletion of your data.</li>
            <li>Object to or restrict certain processing.</li>
            <li>Withdraw consent where processing relies on consent.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            To exercise these rights, contact us using the details below. We may
            need to verify your identity before fulfilling requests.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">8. Security</h2>
          <p>
            We use reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect
            your data, including hashed passwords and restricted access. No
            method of transmission is 100% secure.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">9. International Transfers</h2>
          <p>
            Your information may be processed and stored in locations outside
            your country. We take steps to ensure appropriate safeguards are in
            place.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">10. Third‑Party Links</h2>
          <p>
            DRIVVA may contain links to third‑party sites. We are not
            responsible for their privacy practices. Review their policies when
            visiting.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">11. Children’s Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            DRIVVA is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly
            collect personal information from children under 13.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">12. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this policy from time to time. We will post the
            updated version here and update the “Last updated” date.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">13. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            If you have questions or requests regarding this policy, contact us
            at
            <a href="mailto:support@drivva.example">support@drivva.example</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
